caption: I’ve been taking the Metra more to go to Harvard.  I live in Edgewater so I take the bus to get here. I was hoping there would be a place better than Dunkin Doughnuts to stop at and there was. It is a great little place to have a Lavender Almond Milk Latte and take a minute before I go on the next part of my journey. They have a tasty cafe menu, alcoholic beverages (if you want) and access to free WiFi. Thank you being here and being friendly.
Veggie bagel sandwich is the best thing I've had here. All coffees are amazing , i recommend maple latte and caramel frappe.
Great spot with good drinks and food. Friendly staff and even cocktails.
Awesome place to grab a coffee before work.
No one can beat their excellent customer service, good coffee, and affordable prices. The staffs was very talented, impressive, and professional.
Awesome place. I love coming here for lunch. Their sandwiches are so tasty! Only thing to complain about is that they close too early!!
I like their set up!!  Tasty breakfast!!  Nice seeing a new place on Milwaukee Avenue!!
The coffee is great and the people are kind. That's all one really wants in a coffee shop. Please give your money to them instead of big chains (lookin' at you, Starbucks).
I like to go there for their lavender cardamom latte and breakfast burrito. Need to try other items too soon.
Love the small, cozy vibe. The coffee is not strong at all though.
Just ok
Best place for a cup of coffee in the neighborhood. If only it opened before 7:30 on weekdays...

A wonderful coffee shop with fantastic baristas, delicious sandwiches and snacks as well as a great selection of beers. Perfect place to stop on the way to work for fueling up and on the way home for winding down.

Great little coffee shop in Jefferson Park, right next door to the Popeyes and across from the CTA Blue Line Train Stop.  They typically brew metropolis coffee, so if you are a fan of them this is your place. Coffee shop is still take out only. No seats inside yet due to pandemic, and no outdoor seating. Regardless, they make a great cup. I asked for a caramel macchiato, which they happily accommodated since it wasn't listed on their menu. Prices are fair and the coffee was great. Definitely will try em out again when in the area!
This place is over priced and small proportions. The mocha frappuccino was 2/3 whipped cream.
Nice, local coffee place. I wish I saw special drinks before I placed the order. The list should be on better seen place.
One of the best breakfast burritos I’ve ever had.
This was one of the most delicious breakfast burritos EVER! Irena made a couple of perfect, fluffy egg, masterpieces! Will definitely come back again.
Loved it! Very friendly & helpful lady behind the counter.

I'm a tough critic, but this place has bomb donuts and even better coffee. This is the only place I can drink my coffee black and enjoy its notes. The cold brew is also nice and strong. Definitely stop in, it's across the street from the Jefferson Park blue line.

Super place.  Great owner that actually cares.  All the staff are super friendly and put together a great cup of joe!  It's a special place and real gem in Jefferson Park!  I did not realize it, but they are open during the pandemic.  Support this awesome local business... :)
Super friendly baristas, that actually know what they’re doing! Had one of the best cappuccinos I’ve ever had, definitely a great change from Starbucks. This place rocks!

we did the Lake Effect Brewery (Wednesday Mashup Special) Beer & Donuts. Donuts were from Westons Coffee & Tap.  Donuts were amazing!  A special treat during this social distancing time.  Cake donuts with glaze or with chocolate were so very tasty!  Thank you!
Private party for Cheryl's 40th was outstanding!

We were guests a private birthday party here. Staff was friendly, the beer on tap was chosen by the person throwing the party. My choice of beer for the night was Lake Effect. My wife did not enjoy the Cabernet. Small appetizers were ok, sandwiches were delicious.
Great place with great food.
Amazing coffee and great art in the cup!

This place is awesome. It has everything a small cafe should have. From coffee to wine, they even make sandwiches. It’s very continently located right across the street from the blue line. It also has a friendly staff, especially Paul he’s such a down to earth guy, makes the best cappuccino.
Wonderful spot for specialty coffee, craft beer, and delicious food.

I only had tea & this was my first visit. But I am really looking forward to lunch there this weekend. I already have my food & coffee picked out. The young man behind the counter was helpful & patient answering all my questions!
I can't wait to see what this place is going to be like within a few years... This place rocks and its location is superb!

I'm so glad we have this place in our neighborhood. Fantastic spot to enjoy a cub of coffee and read, work or just people watch going in and out of Jeff Park Station. I meet with my clients there all the time and vibe is perfect for a meeting. Always roomy enough to find the table, the atmosphere is great with a modern feel and they can order coffee or beer if they wish. Speaking of beer. Good rotating selection on tab and it's fun to spontaneously stop by for a pint during the happy hour.
The breakfast burrito is dank. It's a delicious and nutritious choice 😁
That was a solid breakfast burrito.
We really love coming here! The staff are really nice and they have great speciality coffees. They had a unique one with rosemary that was so good.
Great espresso and paninis! I stop here every time I have the chance
This place is a gem. The coffee is amazing, the atmosphere and ambiance has a chill, studious vibe. Super convenient location across the train station... I love it. Highly recommended.
This place is so amazing. Breakfast burrito and great beer.
Great Latte.. Thanks!
Go local, decent coffee. Counter help are pleasant.
Great service

A really cute little place. I haven't had a chance to try their food yet even though they have a pretty full menu and also alcoholic beverages. I love their seasonal coffee drinks, they are festive and the staff is nice.
Loved the coffee. We went on May 4th (May the Fourth) and they gave us Star Wars designed coffees.

Red Maple is such a cute little gem of a cafe I just found in Burbank!! It's towards the Toluca Lake side. It has a cute cozy feel with a nice well decorated outdoor patio. Red Maple is the type of cafe where you order up front, get a number and then sit down.
Perfect location, great service, and excellent coffee!
Nice place, good coffee, right by the blue line!
Excellent espresso, baked goods, and a small but surprising draft beer list. Great service too.
Delicious turmeric late.😍
Friendly staff, relaxed feel. I have tried their sandwiches, coffee and tea. Would go back.
Excellent coffee, chill atmosphere, fine service
Great Lavender Latte and nice tables to bring your laptop/work. Very clean.

Really like this spot: super cute and its not too deep in the city. I have tried the Lavender Latte which is delicious and the Masala Chai latte and an Americano. They also have plenty of outlets for laptops making it a great spot for studying. My ONLY recommendation is to add coconutmilk as another non-dairy alternative (tastes really good with lattes, doesnt add the nuttiness that almondmilk does). Either way though I still enjoyed their lattes with the almondmilk and will continue coming here and trying all of their drinks Highly recommend :) And staff is great!!
Quiet and good sandwiches and peach tea before getting train to O'hare airport.

They have special parking spots for pickups. Never takes them more than 15 minutes to have your order ready very in and out good food but a little overpriced. The chicken is also never cooked all the way but it's something I never order as adds up.
Westons is the best spot in the neighborhood and my go-to place for morning latte and avocado toast! Barista Irena is doing a great job👍

This place is a staple for me. It's a short walk from my apartment, the employees are really friendly, decent sandwiches, good donuts and the coffee -which I don't normally have strong opinions about- is fantastic. If I had any suggestions I'd say more options on chips with your sandwich but beyond that I've got nothing.
Really laid back place where you can get a coffee.or a good local craft beer
Delicious guava matcha frappe!

Weston's gives the clean feel of a Starbucks combined with the home style of a mom and pop shop with chalk menus and care in their coffee preparation. I walked in just as they opened and ordered a drip coffee to go and the person working there that early morning was sociable and talked with me as I asked about the different beans they use. The coffee was Brazilian and tasted great on my morning commute. Definitely the pick up I needed to start my (early) morning! Can't wait to try the rest of their menu
Cute place, good coffee, friendly staff, well worth skipping Starbucks for...
Got the avocado & tomato toast and it was amazing. Coffee was also very good. I would definitely recommend this place!

Walking passed this shop with my son and glad we decided to stop in. What an Adorable coffee shop. Loved the art work. We had some Great coffee and a blueberry bliss tea. Awesome customer service. Clean establishment.
Cozy and warm place for coffee or even for a glass of  wine the Prosciutto and avocado sandwich was good
Dope!

Great place with friendly staff. Always a pleasure. Would definitely recommend. Will note that the sign is confusing. Seems it used to be 730 and is now 7 but the white out is splotchy. This makes it so that it's likely going to take a person coming at 710 a minute (and maybe a few pulls on the door) to understand. The 30 is still much more prominent than the splotchy white behind it. Y'all should like paste or paint an even square over the 30 completely covering it because it is still quite visible. Only reason for 4 stars, But I'll change it when the signs more clear.
Great coffee, food and service !
Great, almost hidden spot, due to the heavy Milwaukee Ave traffic.  Really good coffee, sandwiches, beer and wine...
Cool place with unique menu
Awesome spot off the Jefferson Park blue line - super courteous staff, killer coffee, and great food. Not to mention the happy hour specials of some of Chicago's best local craft beer!

I was served hot coffee that was delicious and up to my expectations. They have some fun flavors like lavender which seem amazing. This location is close to the Jefferson Park blue line so a nice grab and go joint
Their avocado toast is yummy

While it may be a bit more pricey than your average chain Coffee Joint, the product they serve is delicious! 10 out of 10 do recommend the lavender latte. The atmosphere is charming, and the location is very walkable from the Metra station. The only downside for me was that there was not designated parking for the specific place, but street parking was fairly easy.
Nice place not too crowded on Saturday
Neighborhood Anchor all day, morning coffee, sandwich, afternoon tea, evening drink
Great local, small coffee house. Great tasting coffee!
Great coffee, tasty food, craft beer, & more. On the walls are intriguing maps of CTA public transit system over the decades.

UPDATED 2/15/2019 i decided to increase the stars from 2 to 4. this is a high quality place now. still room for improvement but the place is good!  i used to come here only when i didn't have other options. now it's one of my top choices in the area for caffeine or a quick bit  to eat.  for those keeping score at home this place still has the following pros/pluses: location, vibe, very good drip coffee, fast.  good changes i've notice in the past couple months:  - more consistent quality on the barista-made drinks! not amazing but good. i still think the espresso drinks are a bit overpriced ... but with quality more consistent the prices are in the reasonable range now.  - better food options including toasts. it used to be a big deli sandwich or nothing (basically).  - music/vibe. they ditched the louder more aggressive music. now it's indie (mumford & sons etc) or chill dance music.  - beer. i didn't give them enough credit for carrying a small selection of really good local beers on tap. still a little expensive but they get plus points here.  OLD 2-STAR REVIEW BELOW  i take the jeff park blue line so i stop here fairly often just based on location. have been here maybe a dozen times since it opened.  i have held off on writing this negative review b/c i really want this place to do well... otoh i really want the place to make better coffee (or charge less!). so here goes.  Pros: - location. great if you like to stop for coffee on your way to the train or are looking for a spot near CTA. - clean space, warm, good vibe, though the music is often a little more aggressive than I like for a cafe (heavy 90s alt-rock, some metal). to each his own on the music. - usually not a long line in the morning! so you can grab a quick drip coffee. - the drip coffee is high quality. better than starbucks, but not as good as truly high-end places in hipper Chicago neighborhoods like Logan Square or Wicker Park  Cons: - prices!! drinks are priced as if this place staffed with only highly trained baristas serving only high-end coffees. it isn't. prices average $1 more per drink than other far nw side places that do coffee well (Perkolator, Portage Grounds, Cafe Urbano...) - quality control on espresso drinks. drink quality is very hit or miss. i've had some top notch espresso here, and other times some really bottom-of-the barrell stuff. i've ordered up and down the menu--americano, latte, cap, macchiato. it's really luck of the draw. but trends toward poorly done--i've been satisfied maybe 20% of the time? and when you're charging $5 for a small drink (as Weston does after tax + a fifty cent tip), that is not ok.  Not enough data: - ordered sandwich once. was nothing to write home about. just a basic deli sandwich. - small but interesting selection of beers. again kind of overpriced (like $6  for a 12 oz pour. in jeff park? seriously?) but the two times i grabbed a beer it was poured well.  honestly if the location for this place wasn''t so damn convenient i wouldn't come here because of the high prices, combined with truly spotty quality on the espresso drinks.  i REALLY hope they improve... do some training for the baristas, create a culture where quality matters... or lower the prices.
Great food and coffee, but very overpriced.
Great place for coffee, but not only.. Good selection of wine and beer as well.  Plus one of the best Irish coffee I ever tried. Very friendly customer service.
Great neighborhood spot for a great cup of coffee
Bagels, coffee and beer oh my!
Good
Very nice staff and delicious teas! It’s a fairly cozy place
Not enough small coffee shops.  This is a great place for some brew.  Stop there often on my commute.
Excellent coffee or specialty coffee drinks. A must stop when using Jefferson Park metro train and bus stop.

Weston's is a great little coffee shop right off the Jeff Park blue like station. There is some street parking but it's paid and limited. The cafe itself serves all the coffee drinks you can imagine along with wine, beer, and cocktails, as well as various sandwiches, bagels, and other breakfast/lunch items. The coffee (metropolis) is good, the staff is nice, free wifi (obviously), and it's a good space to work in. It's also one of the few good coffee shops in the neighborhood. What else you need to know?
love this place

Was a great place to have a sandwich and coffee. A good variety of food options: breakfast sandwiches, bagels, muffins, etc. Tea and coffee options are plentiful as well. Great location across the street from Jefferson Park Transit terminal. Serves liquor as well for a happy hour treat. Good luck and hope business is great!
Cold Brew was great. Spent a few hours working from here and couldn't have had a better experience. Nice and close to the jp blue line.
Flavorful cup of coffee and nice little hang out spot.
Cute coffee shop with a great staff and a great menu!
The staff here is awesome. I always stop in and they always make me an awesome latte. Great place to chill and hang.
Great coffee in an unexpected, nice little shop

I can not stress how much I live this place! The frappuccinos are good, the chai iced lattes are amazing! (If your a fan of cinnamon) The donuts are amazing not like Dunkin they are so much better! The sandwiches are good, even though I am not a fan of the mustard they make there but if you like tangy you will like there sandwiches. The building is beautiful and I love the seating, there is a bar, some seats set up by the window, and more seats in the back. The staff is so nice and they make you feel so welcomed! Great place, I will be coming back!
Love them.

Such a great gem and addition to the area! It’s a great place with just enough background noise for studying. Great coffee, delicious sandwiches, and their craft beer selection is awesome (definitely go during happy hour 🤗)  Will definitely continue to go back :)
Closes at 7PM .
Delicious tea!
Awesome place for a quick bite and a coffee or a beer.  They have a couple of nice brews on tap.

Amazing gem in the heart of Jeff Park! I had their iced vegan horchata latte- not too sweet, but sweetly refreshing with just the right amount of get-up-and-go. Great atmosphere & friendly service, too.
Great little place. Awesome breakfast
Best coffee in town
Good coffee. Lots of seating available. Quite and clean.
Best coffee in town. And they have wine too. Good place some food options.
Great staff owner Nick is a great guy!  Sevice and coffee are excellent also.
Good coffee, I usually get Americanos, but I got a Con Leche, and it was great. Much stronger than most milk drinks I've had before.
Outstanding..  coffee shop with liquor.
Great sandwiches.....and bathrooms!
A comfortable and friendly place.
Very cool environment; good coffee and tea. Not too boougie :)
Great service. Good coffee. Damn good salad (even if it’s not on the menu).
Excellent coffee & service. A much needed addition to Jefferson Park.

Great service, lovely addition to this decrepit area, and decent eats. They have happy hour (wine, craft beer canned and draft) a small retail selection, a customer restroom, and a perfect noise level for peaceful afternoons reading or working. Conveniently located next to the Jefferson Park Blue Line Station and all relevant bus lines. I will be back.
Great coffee shop. Small, but stellar craft beer selection
Friendly owner, lovely staff, great food and and drinks, in a new, clean, and comfortable setting.  Enjoyed my experience, will be regular!!
Good coffee and craft beers on draft. Nice space.
Apple fritter was decent but coffee is no good. too fruity and acidic. Ambiance was nice, though
Tasty coffee
What is to say? Sells itself as a coffee shop, but you might walk out after a nice pint and a panini with a broad smile!
Clean cafe with fresh food and Metropolis Coffee! Right across from Jefferson Park Transit Center.
Super chill spot convenient to Jeff park transit hub. Lots of seating, nice baked goods selection, WIFI, friendly staff. Not the cheapest prices, but will def return!

Weston's is a great addition to the community. It's modern but not pretentious with enough coffee and sandwiches for most folks. Went with my partner and young child and staff were fairly helpful and creative in making steamed juice. The problems we had seemed to stem from being a newer place while they are training needs staff. I'd love to come back and see how they iron out the kinks of a changing menu, staff learning systems, etc. Thanks for opening Weston's. We will be back.
New spot across from the Jeff Park CTA terminal. Excellent coffee and friendly staff. Good selection of sandwiches and pastries. Good spot to chill between trains.
Great stop for morning coffee or evening beer.
Donuts were so-so.   Then again you wouldn't come here for donuts alone.   Go for the beverages.
Glad this place opened right across Milwaukee from my train stop! Went for morning coffee and after-work beer. They had Great Lake's Christmas beer on tap! Whoa!
Great cuppa coffee! Smooth as silk.
Friendly staff, great drink options for anytime of day. Perfectly located across from Jefferson Park Transit Center.
It wouldn’t be fair to rate on their service or food as I was there for a soft opening. However, I was impressed with the service and food. I suggest stopping by and checking them out.
